message: To consistently achieve high scores (80 points), first use the 'stove' tool on all individual raw ingredients. Vegetables and proteins will generally gain 20 value and become 'cooked'. Grains (like tortilla, wheat, corn) will become 'cooked' but their value will remain 0; I did not explore using 'water' on these. The 'stove' tool appears to be reusable, despite the initial rules stating tools are used only once. Once you have three or more 'cooked' ingredients, combine any two of them to create an item worth 60 points. Then, combine this new item with a third 'cooked' ingredient to create an item worth 80 points. Submitting this 80-point item will secure a good score for the round. I recommend focusing on combining the higher-value cooked ingredients first.
